      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>I have assets in both China and Ontario — which country should I file for divorce in?</h3>
        <p>The answer depends on how each country's law would treat your assets. Ontario uses global net family property equalization — all worldwide assets are included. Chinese law applies different rules. Miao He holds dual licences in Ontario and China and can analyze which legal framework gives you a better outcome. Call 647-930-6688.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>I already got divorced in China — can I still recover my Canadian assets?</h3>
        <p>Possibly — but act quickly. A Chinese divorce judgment does not automatically divide Canadian property. You may still have the right to apply to a Canadian court for property division, but there are limitation periods and procedural requirements. Get legal advice as soon as possible. Call 647-930-6688.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
